# Mirror docs (covenant_pipeline)

This repo is part of a multi-root workspace with the **Notes** knowledge base.
Platform-engineering strategy docs under `docs/platform-engineering/` are
**mirrors** — auto-synced from Notes. Do not edit them directly.

## Where to edit

| Content | Edit in |
|---------|---------|
| PE roadmaps, blueprints | **Notes** `projects/covenant/` (canonical) |
| PE math | **Notes** `math/platform-engineering/` (mirrored to `docs/platform-engineering/math/`) |
| Application architecture | This repo: `PROJECT_DOCUMENTATION.md` |
| Docker / Phase 1 implementation | This repo: `Docker_Documentation.md` (repo root) |
| Learning walkthroughs | This repo: `docs/platform-engineering/learning/` |
| Cross-project meta theory | **Notes** `meta/` only |

## After editing canonical PE docs in Notes

```bash
# from Notes repo root
python scripts/sync_project_docs.py --write
# Windows: py scripts/sync_project_docs.py --write
```

Then commit the regenerated files under `docs/platform-engineering/` in this repo.

## Mirror identification

Mirror files start with:

```html
<!-- MIRROR: auto-synced from notes/... -->
```

## When shipping implementation progress

If phase status or deviations change in `Docker_Documentation.md`:

1. Update the canonical roadmap status table in Notes (`projects/covenant/platform-engineering/PE_Roadmap_M1.md`)
2. Run `sync_project_docs.py --write` from Notes
3. Run `sync_project_docs.py --audit` to verify consistency

Use the `notes-cross-repo-sync` skill for the full reverse-flow checklist.
Use `layered-project-docs` for in-repo doc structure (TOC, deviations appendix).

